  Fire away, Nissim вҖ” I'm ready to dig! рҹҺҜ

вқҜ today all batbern organizers met in a teams call, and we where discussing the topic for the next event in summer. Somehow the      
  current implementation of topic selection with the topic heatmap was not helpfull. Not dynamic and not fast enough. We had no      
  overview of what our partners said they where interested in. And the current heatmap is so static and just shows some              
  categorisation of topics, and when such events where.                                                                              
                                                                                                                                     
  People throw in a sugestion and then we would immediately like to see how close this is to what our Partners said, how long ago in 
   terms of number of BATbern events, the last BATbern event on similar topics where, and also what the Swiss IT conference          
  landscape has planned on this topic, to not overlap.                                                                               
                                                                                                                                     
  Also when we have no ideas, the topics that we have in our backlog, combined with the topics given and voted by our Partners       
  should already give a nice view of possible next topics.                                                                           
                                                                                                                                     
  I was envisioning something like the game blob. do you know it. bllobs swim around the void, and you have to try to swallow other  
  blobs, then you get bigger and bigger. i thought, that a possible topic, could be a blue blob.                                     
                                                                                                                                     
  we have 9 partners. if every partner has one or two distinct topics, this would make at most 20 green blobs, that get attracted to 
   blue blobs, if the topics match (not word for word, but are similar (using ai to understand if its similar or not). if it         
  matches, then the green blob gets swallowed by the topic blob and the partner name is now floating in the topic blob, indicating,  
