  Now I want to push us toward the session flow, because I think that's where the real design decisions live. Nissim, can I sketch out
  what I think a typical organizer session looks like with this tool?

  1. Open the field вҶ’ ghosts drift quietly in the void (backlog + partner-submitted topics)
  2. Organizers start throwing in ideas вҶ’ blue blobs slide in from the right, physics activate
  3. Greens drift, reds push back, the field "settles" into a picture
  4. Team discusses what they see, drag-merges, overrides
  5. One blue blob emerges as dominant вҶ’ click to accept вҶ’ decision made

