  All three are latent. All three can be awakened with a click. But they have different provenance вҖ” and a subtle visual cue (shimmer,
  tint) tells you where an idea came from without needing a label. When a trend ghost gets awakened and immediately pulls 4 partner blobs
   toward it, that's a signal so strong you'd almost feel embarrassed not choosing it.

  And 3 events/year вҶ’ 6 events = 2 years. That's the right calibration. Recency feels human-scale. Two years is genuinely "recent" in a
  professional community. The red star only lights up if it's within that 2-year window. Beyond that вҖ” it fades into the cosmic
  background. I love it.

