  рҹҺЁ Sally: And with single-driver confirmed, I can sharpen the interaction design significantly. The driver is probably a technically
  comfortable organizer who knows the keyboard. So here's my refined interaction spec:

  Keyboard-first for the driver:
  - Type anywhere on the canvas вҶ’ a text input appears вҶ’ Enter spawns the blue blob from the right edge
  - Escape to cancel typing
  - Ctrl+Z to remove the last blob (undo)
  - Space while hovering a ghost вҶ’ awakens it

  Mouse for manipulation:
  - Click a blob вҶ’ selection ring appears, shows its details (event number, partner names, etc.)
  - Hold + drag вҶ’ move blob, trigger manual merge if held close enough for 1.5s
  - Double-click a blue blob вҶ’ opens the "accept topic" confirmation вҶ’ generates the session note

  For the watchers on the Teams call:
  - Large, readable labels. Partner logos minimum 32px even when floating inside a blue blob.
  - No tooltips вҖ” those only work for the driver's cursor. Everything the watchers need must be in the blob itself.
  - High contrast dark background. The navy void with bright-colored blobs will survive screen-share compression far better than a light
  theme.

  рҹ“Ҡ Mary to Sally: The "no tooltips" constraint is really smart. Screen-share kills hover states. Everything needs to be legible at 720p
   stream quality.

